    "instruction": "For Tomcat04 only: using full-series data compute global p50 and p95 for these keys if present: trace.self.duration_mean, trace.self.duration_p95, log.row_count, log.gc_pause_max, log.error_count, OSLinux-CPU_CPU_CPUCpuUtil (or similar CPU util KPI), JVM-Memory_7778_JVM_Memory_HeapMemoryUsed, JVM-Memory_7778_JVM_Memory_HeapMemoryUsage. Then filter each Tomcat04 series to the incident window 2021-03-10 17:30:00 — 2021-03-10 18:00:00 (UTC+8) and find the earliest timestamp where (value >= global_p95) AND (value > global_p50 * 1.5). For each key that meets this stricter anomaly rule, return a CSV-like row: metric_name,global_p50,global_p95,earliest_anomaly_timestamp,anomaly_value. Limit output to top 20 rows. Also return up to 20 raw trace.csv rows for Tomcat04 within the window (columns: timestamp,trace_name,value) sorted by timestamp to help confirm trace timing. Keep outputs compact."
